{"title_page": "Orders, decorations, and medals of Namibia", "text_new": "The '''Republic of [[Namibia]]''' has an honours system comprising orders, medals, military decorations, and police decorations.  Legislation also provides for the establishment of decorations and medals for the intelligence service,<ref name=isa>[http://www.saflii.org  Namibia Central Intelligence Service Regulations] (''Government Gazette'' 1876 (5 June 1998))</ref> the prisons service,<ref name=pris>[http://www.saflii.org  Regulations for the Administration and Control of the Namibian Prisons Service] (''Government Gazette'' 2643 (8 November 2001))</ref> and the fire services.<ref name=fire>[http://www.saflii.org  Local Authorities Fire Brigade Services Act 2006] (''Government Gazette'' 3760 (29 December 2006))</ref>\n\nThese honours and awards superseded those used by the then territory of [[South West Africa]] before independence in 1990.\n\n==Orders==\n[[File:Namibian orders.gif|right|266px|]]\n\nThe following orders are conferred by the President of Namibia:<ref name=hons>[http://www.saflii.org/na/other/NAGovGaz/1995/19.pdf Proclamation No 2 of 1995] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928233617/http://www.saflii.org/na/other/NAGovGaz/1995/19.pdf |date=2013-09-28 }} (''Government Gazette'' 1048 (17 March 1995))</ref>\n\n* '''Order of the Most Ancient ''[[Welwitschia]] mirabilis'' ''' (1995- ) &mdash; for the President and other heads of state.\n* '''Most Brilliant Order of the Sun''' (born 1995) &mdash; for meritorious service.\n* '''Most Excellent Order of the Eagle''' (born 1995) &mdash; for diplomatic services.\n* '''Order of the Mukorob''' (born 1995) &mdash; for meritorious military service.\n* '''Most Distinguished Order of Namibia''' (born 1995) &mdash; for meritorious service.\n\n==Medals==\n\n* '''Independence Medal''' (1995) &mdash; to commemorate the independence of Namibia in 1990.\n* '''Liberation Medal''' (1995) &mdash; for services connected with the liberation of Namibia from South African administration.\n\n==Namibian Defence Force==\n[[File:Namibian Defence Force medal ribbons.gif|right|244px|]]\n\nThe [[Namibian Defence Force]] has the following decorations and medals:\n\n* '''Namibian Cross for Bravery: Gold'''\n* '''Namibian Cross for Bravery: Silver'''\n* '''Namibian Cross for Bravery: Bronze'''\n---\n* '''Campaign Medal''' &mdash; for service in military operations, e.g. in [[East Timor]] and [[Sierra Leone]].\n* '''Medal of Honour''' &mdash; presented to the next-of-kin of NDF personnel who are killed on service.\n---\n* '''Service Medal: Gold''' &mdash; for 30 years service in the NDF.\n* '''Service Medal: Silver''' &mdash; for 20 years service in the NDF.\n* '''Service Medal: Bronze''' &mdash; for 10 years service in the NDF.\n---\n* '''Namibian Champion Shot Medal''' &mdash; for the winners of the annual shooting championships.\n\n===Namibian Army===\nThe [[Namibian Army]] has the following decorations and medals:\n* '''Army Pioneer Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/gen-kadhila</ref>\n* '''Army 10 years service Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/gen-kadhila</ref>\n* '''Army 20 years service Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/gen-kadhila</ref>\n* '''Operation Mandume campaign Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/gen-kadhila</ref>\n* '''Army Commendation Medal'''\n\n===Namibian Navy===\nThe [[Namibian Navy]] has the following decorations and medals:\n* '''Navy Pioneer Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Southern Cross Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Navy Cross Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Gold Star Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Sacharia Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Achievement Medal '''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''Ten Year Service'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''750 Days at Sea Service Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/permanent-secretary</ref>\n* '''250 Days at Sea Service Medal'''<ref>http://www.mod.gov.na/documents/264813/286599/profile+of+Bamba+navy+commander.pdf/da0fd5bb-9c27-48f2-af75-dfa20e658438</ref>\n\n===Namibian Air Force===\nThe [[Namibian Air Force]] has the following decorations and medals:\n* '''Air Force Pioneer Medal'''\n* '''Air Force 10 years service Medal'''\n* '''Air Force 20 years service Medal'''\n\n==Namibian Police Force==\n[[File:Namibian Police Force medal ribbons.gif|right|244px|]]\n\nThe [[Namibian Police Force]] has the following decorations and medals<ref name=npf>[http://www.saflii.org  Regulations relating to the award of decorations and medals to members of the Namibian Police Force] (''Government Gazette'' 2997 (20 June 2003)</ref>\n\n* '''NP Cross of Honour''' (CH) (2003- ) &mdash; for a very exceptional death-defying act of conspicuous bravery.\n* '''NP Cross for Bravery''' (CB) (2003- ) &mdash; for an act of bravery in great danger.\n* '''Decoration for Outstanding Meritorious Svce of the Highest Order''' (OMS) (2003- ) &mdash; for outstanding meritorious service of the highest order (officers only).\n* '''Decoration for Outstanding Meritorious Service and Utmost Devotion to Duty''' (DSD) (2003- ) &mdash; for outstanding meritorious service and utmost devotion to duty (other ranks only).\n* '''Commendation Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; for special service of a high order.\n---\n* '''Campaign Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; for service in operations.\n* '''Medal of Honour''' (2003- ) &mdash; presented to the next-of-kin of NPF personnel who are killed in the execution of their duties.\n* '''Wound Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; for being severely wounded in the execution of duty.\n---\n* '''NP Service Medal: Gold''' (2003- ) &mdash; for 30 years service in the NPF.\n* '''NP Service Medal: Silver''' (2003- ) &mdash; for 20 years service in the NPF.\n* '''NP Service Medal: Bronze''' (2003- ) &mdash; for 10 years service in the NPF.\n* '''Reservist Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; for 5 years service as a police reservist.\n* '''Honourable Discharge Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; awarded on honourable discharge from the NPF.\n---\n* '''President's Shottist Medal''' (2003- ) &mdash; for the winners of the annual shooting championships.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130331205521/http://sahw.hwmw.net46.net/ South African Medals Website]\n{{Decorations by country}}\n\n[[Category:Orders, decorations, and medals of Namibia| ]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Republic of [[Namibia]]''' has an honours system comprising orders, medals, military decorations, and police decorations.  Legislation also provides for the establishment of decorations and medals for the intelligence service,<ref name=isa>[http://www.saflii.org  Namibia Central Intelligence Service Regulations] (''Government Gazette'' 1876 (5 June 1998))</ref> the prisons service,<ref name=pris>[http://www.saflii.org  Regulations for the Administration and Control of the Namibian Prisons Service] (''Government Gazette'' 2643 (8 November 2001))</ref> and the fire services.<ref name=fire>[http://www.saflii.org  Local Authorities Fire Brigade Services Act 2006] (''Government Gazette'' 3760 (29 December 2006))</ref>\n\nThese honours and awards superseded those used by the then territory of [[South West Africa]] before independence in 1990.\n\n==Orders==\n[[File:Namibian orders.gif|right|266px|]]\n\nThe following orders are conferred by the President of Namibia:<ref name=hons>[http://www.saflii.org/na/other/NAGovGaz/1995/19.pdf Proclamation No 2 of 1995] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928233617/http://www.saflii.org/na/other/NAGovGaz/1995/19.pdf |date=2013-09-28 }} (''Government Gazette'' 1048 (17 March 1995))</ref>\n\n* '''Order of the Most Ancient ''[[Welwitschia]] mirabilis'' ''' (1995- ) &mdash; for the President and other heads of state.\n* '''Most Brilliant Order of the Sun'''